The paper discusses CP-nets and CI-nets, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence for representing and reasoning about preferences. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves some computational aspects, which suggest that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also touches upon game theory, which is covered in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and multi-agent systems, which are discussed in cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
